1************
 * UT423    *
 ************
0UT423
 -----
01. PURPOSE
 ----------
0   NORMALLY, IF IT IS REQUIRED TO CREATE AN EMPTY FILE WHICH IS SUBSEQUENTLY
    TO BE GIVEN A DISPOSITION OF MOD, IT IS NECESSARY EITHER TO WRITE A SMALL
    PROGRAM TO DO IT, OR TO WRITE A DUMMY FIRST RECORD USING ONE OF THE
    STANDARD UTILITIES SUCH AS IEBGENER OR UT361.
0   THE PURPOSE OF THIS UTILITY IS TO EMPTY (BY ISSUING AN OPEN AND A CLOSE
    WITHOUT AN INTERVENING WRITE) ANY SEQUENTIAL FILE, WHILE PRESERVING THE
    CORRECT DATA SET ATTRIBUTES IN THE DATA SET LABEL.
02. LIMITATIONS
 --------------
0   THE UTILITY MAY BE APPLIED ONLY TO SEQUENTIAL FILES.
03. INPUT DATA
 -------------
0   NONE.
04. OUTPUT DATA
 --------------
0   1.   THE EMPTIED DATA SET.
    2.   A MESSAGE ON THE CONSOLE TYPEWRITER OF THE FORM.
0        THE FOLLOWING FILE HAS BEEN EMPTIED - A....................A
05. OPERATION
 ------------
0   THE JOB CONTROL STATEMENTS REQUIRED TO INVOKE THE UTILITY ARE
    //   EXEC      PGM=UT423
    //EOFILE  DD   DSN=................
